{{see|Bay}}
{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
*bā, /beɪ/, /<tt>beI</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-eɪ|Rhymes: -eɪ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#(''geography'') A [[body of water]] more or less [[three-quarters]] [[surround]]ed by land.
#A [[compartment]] or area surrounded on three sides.
#A [[brown]] [[colour]]/[[color]] of the [[coat]] of some [[horse]]s.
#A [[shrub]] of the family ''[[Lauraceae]]'', the source of the herb of the same name.
#The [[herb]] derived from the shrub of the same name.
#The distance between two supports in a [[vault]].
#(''nautical'') Each of the spaces, [[port]] and [[starboard]], between [[deck]]s, forward of the [[bitt]]s, in [[sailing]] [[warship]]s
#(''colour'')a reddish brown colour.
#:<table><tr><td>bay colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#6F4E37" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>

===Adjective===
'''bay'''
#(''colour'') of a reddish brown colour.

====Synonyms====
*(''body of water''): [[gulf]]
*(''shrub''): [[bay laurel]], [[Grecian laurel]], [[laurel]], [[sweet bay]], [[true laurel]]

